{
  "texts": [
    "(12)The baseline GR model consists of the modes {(2, 2), (3, 3)}, and each hypothesis is constructed from this basic model with the deviation parameters contained in the subscript of each hypothesis.",
    "We neglect the deviations δτ 33, since damping times (and so their deviations) are in general more difficult to be measured than the frequencies.",
    "As in Sect. 5.3, we repeat the analysis by varying the starting time across the 95% CI of the IMR peaktime distribution.",
    "This amounts to \"marginalise\" a-posteriori over the start time uncertainty.",
    "The results are shown in Figs. 4, 7, 10, 11."
  ]
}